Bundled EU national legal MCP connectors (desktop installer)
------------------------------------------------------------

The desktop installer additionally bundles nine national EU legal MCP
connectors, each in a separate repository under the Apache License 2.0
(distinct from the MIT connectors above; Apache-2.0 is compatible with
AGPL-3.0 for distribution):

  - de-eli-mcp, at-eli-mcp, es-eli-mcp, fi-eli-mcp, ie-eli-mcp,
    nl-eli-mcp, se-eli-mcp, fr-eli-mcp, lu-eli-mcp
  - Copyright (c) 2026 MateMatic Solutions / Wiesław Mazur
  - Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
  - https://github.com/matematicsolutions/<name>-eli-mcp

These connectors are Python (fastmcp) and are run from a bundled CPython
runtime (see below). See governance/adr/0136-bundled-python-runtime-eli.md.


Bundled CPython runtime (desktop installer)
-------------------------------------------

To run the Python EU connectors offline without requiring a system Python,
the desktop installer bundles a standalone CPython build:

  - CPython - Python Software Foundation License v2
    https://www.python.org (via python-build-standalone, astral-sh/uv)
  - python-build-standalone - https://github.com/astral-sh/python-build-standalone

Python packages installed into the bundled runtime (resolved at build time):
  - fastmcp (Apache-2.0), mcp (MIT), httpx (BSD-3-Clause),
    pydantic (MIT), anyio (MIT), diskcache (Apache-2.0),
    uvicorn/starlette and transitive dependencies (BSD/MIT/Apache-2.0).
  Their full licenses can be inspected via
  `py-runtime/python.exe -m pip show <package>` or in each package's
  site-packages dist-info.
